<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="11" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="11">
<bibRefCitation author="Friese, H" journalOrPublisher="Freilander &amp; Sohn, Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" refId="B13" refString="Friese, H, 1895. Die Bienen Europas. 1. Schmarotzerbienen. Freilander &amp; Sohn, Berlin" title="Die Bienen Europas. 1. Schmarotzerbienen." year="1895">Friese (1895</bibRefCitation>
: 208) determined some specimens from North Mongolia (without an exact locality) as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nylander" authorityYear="1848" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Epeolus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeolus pictus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Epeolus pictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Nylander, 1848, but noted that these specimens differed from 
<taxonomicName family="Apidae" genus="E." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="E. variegatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" rank="species" species="variegatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">E. variegatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Morawitz, F" journalOrPublisher="Horae Societatis Entomologicae Rossicae" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" pagination="61 - 79" refId="B22" refString="Morawitz, F, 1865. Ueber einige Andrenidae aus der Umgegend von St.-Petersburg. Horae Societatis Entomologicae Rossicae 3 (1): 61 - 79" title="Ueber einige Andrenidae aus der Umgegend von St. - Petersburg." volume="3" year="1865">Morawitz (1865</bibRefCitation>
: 50), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nylander" authorityYear="1848" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Epeolus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeolus pictus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">Epeolus pictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName family="Apidae" genus="E." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="E. variegatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" rank="species" species="variegatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="11">E. variegatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and this is supported by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4437.1.1" author="Bogusch, P" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="11" pagination="1 - 60" refId="B8" refString="Bogusch, P, Hadrava, J, 2018. European bees of the genera Epeolus Latreille, 1802 and Triepeolus Robertson, 1901 (Hymenoptera: Apidae: Nomadinae: Epeolini): taxonomy, identification key, distribution, and ecology. Zootaxa 4437 (1): 1 - 60, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4437.1.1" title="European bees of the genera Epeolus Latreille, 1802 and Triepeolus Robertson, 1901 (Hymenoptera: Apidae: Nomadinae: Epeolini): taxonomy, identification key, distribution, and ecology." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4437.1.1" volume="4437" year="2018">Bogusch and Hadrava (2018)</bibRefCitation>
who re-examined type specimens.
</paragraph>
